# Induction Motor Fault Detection using MCSA & Machine Learning

## ğŸ“Œ Overview
This project implements **Motor Current Signature Analysis (MCSA)** combined with **machine learning** techniques to detect faults in an induction motor. The approach is non-invasive and suitable for condition monitoring.

## âš™ï¸ Faults Detected
- Broken Rotor Bar
- Bearing Inner Race Fault
- Bearing Outer Race Fault
- Healthy Condition

## ğŸ› ï¸ Tools & Technologies
- MATLAB (FFT, signal processing)
- Machine Learning (Random Forest, KNN, etc.)
- Motor Current Signature Analysis (MCSA)

## ğŸ“Š Methodology
1. Stator current acquisition
2. Signal conditioning and FFT
3. Feature extraction in frequency domain
4. ML-based fault classification
5. Performance evaluation using accuracy and confusion matrix

## ğŸ“ˆ Results
- Random Forest and KNN achieved highest accuracy
- Ensemble and instance-based models performed better than linear models

